{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_70","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented FILECOH-004 by splitting the monolithic comparison workflow behind the existing facade. [experiment_comparison_analysis.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_comparison_analysis.py) is now a thin public coordinator and re-export layer, with discovery moved to [experiment_comparison_discovery.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_comparison_discovery.py), scoring/null-test/output assembly moved to [experiment_comparison_core.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_comparison_core.py), packaging/report/UI export work moved to [experiment_comparison_packaging.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_comparison_packaging.py), and shared normalization/version helpers placed in [experiment_comparison_common.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_comparison_common.py). Existing workflow behavior stayed intact, including packaged bundle generation, offline report regeneration from local artifacts, and pre-resolved plan inputs.\n\nAdded a regression check in [test_experiment_comparison_analysis.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_experiment_comparison_analysis.py) to verify the facade re-exports the split discovery/core implementations and that the core module does not import report-generation or bundle-packaging helpers at import time.\n\nVerified with:\n- targeted unittest run over comparison/validation/dashboard/circuit flows: 27 tests passed\n- `make test`: 325 tests passed\n- `make smoke`: 325 tests passed, plus manifest validation for `manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml` again